App Name: Securonix
Version: 1.01
Author: Securonix (www.securonix.com)
Splunkbase URL: https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/3007/
Installation and Configuration document:http://www.securonix.com/SplunkApp
Support Contact:splunkapp-support@securonix.com

Description of the App:
The Securonix App for Splunk provides an Executive, Security Analysts and Operational view of the key metrics derived from the Securonix’ analytics platform.

Prerequisites: (**Described in the Installation and configuration guide**)
1. DBConnect App: The Splunk DB Connect App must be installed. The DB Connect app is available 	for download at https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/958/. 
 
2. Splunk App for Unix: To gather the Server hardware metrics like CPU, Memory and Disk, the Splunk 	app for Unix is required. It can be downloaded from https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/273/. Your organization may have deployed the Unix App already, please consult with your Splunk administrator. 

3. Lookup File: The Securonix App requires a lookup file to be updated with the hostname of all the Securonix Nodes in your environment along with the DB Connect Spec name that will be used to connect to the MySQL database on corresponding Securonix Node. This lookup file contains two columns – “host” (for hostname) and “spec” (for spec name) Lookup file name - lookup_nodes.csv 
Important:  
• The first entry in this lookup file must be that of the Securonix Master node 
• The host name should be the same name with which the Splunk forwarder on the nodes are configured to send logs to Splunk indexers
